=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Tutorials_10-SynthDefs-and-Synths_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 661 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 661.1603
  harmonic_decay_rate: -15.9839
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5007
  pitch_clarity: 98.2992
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -4.9900
  resonance_freq: 667.5293

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: 10. SynthDefs and Synths Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Tutorials/Getting-Started/10-SynthDefs-and-Synths.html
// Tags: 10-SynthDefs-and-Synths, Tutorials
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
x = { SinOsc.ar(660, 0, 0.2) }.play;
y = SynthDef.new("tutorial-SinOsc", { |out| Out.ar(out, SinOsc.ar(440, 0, 0.2)) }).play;
x.free;    // free just x
y.free;    // free just y
